    "excerpt": "An original liturgical poem inspired by the Modah|Modeh Ani prayer.  . . .",
    "content": "\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"/translate/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Contribute a translation</a></th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Source (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng\">\nIn these still, quiet moments,<br />\nI am not asleep<br />\nand not yet awake.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng\">\nIn the threshold of day and night,<br />\nwith the mixture of darkness and light,<br />\nmy body is once again coming to life.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng\">\nI am reborn, each day,<br />\nfrom the womb of your compassion.<br />\nMay all of my actions<br />\nbe worthy of the faith You&#8217;ve placed in me.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng\">\nWith words of thanks I&#8217;ll greet the dawn.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>Thank you to Andrew Shaw for contributing this work inspired by Modah/Modeh Ani. See <a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/prayers/solilunar/everyday/daytime/birkhot-hashahar/modah-modeh-ani-translation-by-andrew-shaw/\">here</a> for Andrew&#8217;s English translation of that prayer.</p>\n",
